reviews.text: Food is overpriced for what it is if you order a la carte. We ordered the value set $268 which includes grilled beef, some sashimi and small appetizers and we added a hot soba with clams. Food was okay. Service was unstable, no one took care of you when you waited outside to be seated and after we were seated, we waited for 5 mins until waiters acknowledged our existence and gave us menu and tea. Waiters seemed busy dashing around but tended to avoid eye contact throughout the meal. I wouldn’t be back as the food was nothing special.
Booking via eatigo but could not order too much food alone 😅
Small place, with good food.

A bit pricey for lunch, they sell cooked Japanese meals and sushi sets. I think this place main featured dish is the cold dipping soba noodles.

I had the beef hotpot for lunch which includes soba and it costed around 180 HKD. In my opinion the food quality is ok, the soba was very refreshing. However, for the price point the actual hotpot was lacking. Mostly comprised of vegetables and they didn't even give you a lot of vegetables. I've been to other places in CWB that serve similar hotpot sets but with a lot more ingredients and vastly cheaper...

Overall, come here for the soba. Acceptable place but on the pricier side for lunch.
Food quality is good.

result.name: Tonkichi とん吉日式吉列豬扒專門店

reviews.text:
今日去左世貿的一間日本菜餐廳,銅鑼灣站行轉眼就到,幾就腳方便,
店內的佈置行高雅深調的日本氛圍,燈光溫和很有格調,
卡位有日本坐墊,居酒屋卡位間隔,私隱度高,
總體環境不錯,地方坐落舒服,聊天聚會是不錯的地方~ .
.
*吉列神戶牛定食 及 吉列豬柳定食
吉列牛肉質非常嫩滑，入口時油脂完全溶化在口，卻又不會蓋過其牛味，脂香肉味並重~麵包糠外皮也炸得酥脆，既不油膩又不甩皮，炸功不錯~
吉列豬柳薄薄一層炸粉，外層炸至金黃酥脆的包糠香脆可口，內裡保留肉嫩新鮮肉味濃郁，份量幾足料，賣相也吸引~
.
前菜伴碟有一些酸瓜類、麵豉湯、白飯、生菜絲 ,擺盤別緻簡潔,
生菜絲和米飯及熱茶可以要求再增添~飯後還有水果西瓜呢~
同埋可以自己落手磨芝麻,磨完芝麻空氣都瀰漫住芝麻的香氣~
.
*梅子膠原蛋白果凍 及 綠茶雪糕伴和果子
梅子醋香甜可口,非常開胃,梅子在口中刺激著味蕾~
膠原蛋白果凍補充我們每日續漸流失的膠原蛋白,
綠茶雪糕香甜滑軟,有着豐厚的綠茶味,
和果子好軟身,外皮Q彈,內裡creamy~
超正! 入咗會。近排再做promotion. 上次食完送咗1張coupon. 免費享受了吉列蠔，再用會員coupon 享受了刺身併盆。再用200元coupon. 落樓只要4百多元食多了吉列大海老。大蝦豬柳。
高水準及美味的日式吉列豬扒套餐，白飯生菜絲任食，還有其他選擇如吉列蝦，蠔及牛。吉列表面鬆化可口，內裹肉質鮮美柔軟唔乾身。晚餐每人消費平均HK$350
Good Food. Slow service.
high quality food but pretty expensive

Nice soba but very busy and will need to wait for a long time. Not all staff are friendly but a few of them are really professional. 

Sadly, today they have missed my order......
Adequate for price charged
Good food quality, small portion

There aren’t that many soba restaurants in Hong Kong so when I crave for soba noodles I come to this place sometimes. Very average soba, price is somewhat reasonable, hey it is not like you got a lot of choices in town anyways.
Kurotaki is a soba specialty restaurant, but they also serve Wagyu beef from Kyoto. The servers are attentive.

reviews.text:
Nice soba but very busy and will need to wait for a long time. Not all staff are friendly but a few of them are really professional. 

Sadly, today they have missed my order......

食物非常美味。 都好抵食。
但係室內烤肉味大，食完成身有啲未。

在香港不止烏冬有專門店～原來蕎麥麵也有的喔
有天剛好逛世貿中心時便發現了這家 - 黑瀧板蕎麥專門店
而且沒想到假日的時間會有午市定食，還完全不需要等位呢
午市定食$158起，會有三款的前菜 + 主食～想轉套餐加飲品的話要+$20
另外定食的蕎麥麵分兩種等級 - 田舍 & 更科 (・∀・) 我們都有點到喲

雜錦壽司配更科蕎麥麵 ($158)
前菜有銀魚沙律 - 這個不是用醋，是用豉油調味吧? 吃落鹹鹹的 ...
唐揚炸雞 - 吃的時候還是熱的，肉貿還很嫩滑～另外亦配了漬物
雜錦壽司 - 畢竟不是壽司店吧～飯沒什麼味 .. 不過尚算新鮮
這個的定食是 更科蕎麥麵 - 口感較為滑身且爽口
和平時見開的蕎麥麵顏色不一樣，這款是白色的喔 

陶板燒牛肉配田舍蕎麥麵 ($188)
前菜有三文魚沙律 - 厚切的三文魚，這沙律倒是用醋調味
汁煮牛舌 - 好軟稔也很入味！另外這個也是有漬物
陶板燒牛肉 - 不止有牛肉，還有配南瓜、菇和蔥
牛肉很有嚼勁，肉汁也滿滿的喲～不過要注意不能燒得太過火
這定食則是 - 田舍蕎麥麵 ～顏色跟平時見開的一樣
口感較為有彈性，配濃厚的麵汁來吃確實不錯
但有部份的麵條黏在一起，還十分硬的 ... 吃的時候要自行分開有點麻煩 

Total：$380.6 (已計加一服務費)
食雲否麵好過，不合口味，，价較贵
環境食物質素幾好, 如果店員能夠講解下佢講下點樣食 蕎麥麵 會更加好

reviews.text: Food is overpriced for what it is if you order a la carte. We ordered the value set $268 which includes grilled beef, some sashimi and small appetizers and we added a hot soba with clams. Food was okay. Service was unstable, no one took care of you when you waited outside to be seated and after we were seated, we waited for 5 mins until waiters acknowledged our existence and gave us menu and tea. Waiters seemed busy dashing around but tended to avoid eye contact throughout the meal. I wouldn’t be back as the food was nothing special.
Booking via eatigo but could not order too much food alone 😅
Small place, with good food.

A bit pricey for lunch, they sell cooked Japanese meals and sushi sets. I think this place main featured dish is the cold dipping soba noodles.

I had the beef hotpot for lunch which includes soba and it costed around 180 HKD. In my opinion the food quality is ok, the soba was very refreshing. However, for the price point the actual hotpot was lacking. Mostly comprised of vegetables and they didn't even give you a lot of vegetables. I've been to other places in CWB that serve similar hotpot sets but with a lot more ingredients and vastly cheaper...

Overall, come here for the soba. Acceptable place but on the pricier side for lunch.
